entry.title: [WebNN][CrOS]: Build infrastructure for converting WebNN graph to tflite model
entry.content:
Add a converter class to convert WebNN graph to tflite model and

persist into FlatBuffer. The schema_generated.h file defines the format

for each data structure to serialize, there are below functions:

1, `SerializeBuffer` is to serialize the constant data (e.g. weights)

2, `SerializeTensor` is to serialize tensor for input, constant and

output operand.

3, `SerializeOperation` is to serialize operations, `Relu` is supported

in this CL.

entry.title: pip-tuck: Implement tuck feature for CrOS PiP
entry.content:
This commit introduces the ability to tuck the Picture-in-Picture (PiP)

window with a fling gesture.



Tucking is a feature originally implemented for floated windows (in

tablet mode). It allows users to conveniently hide away the window

without closing it. When the window is tucked the "tuck handle" (a

button with a small chevron) shows up, which allows users to untuck the

screen.



Originally, the horizontal fling on PiP windows at the screen edge

caused the PiP window to dismiss. With this commit, the behavior has

been changed to PiP tucking. PiP tucking is similar to floated window

tucking, and when tucked the PiP window is hidden except for the width

of the handle. The PiP window should also dim to up to 50% depending on

the user's input. For the design details please see the demo video.



For this feature, we utilize `PipController` to manage the

`PipScopedWindowTucker` and handle tucking / untucking events.



This feature is currently locked behind the flag #enable-pip-tuck.



Demo video:

(https://drive.google.com/file/d/1eTf9bgrToHJBrAO7XkwtCPyWp_N05fg_)

entry.title: [Promise Icons] Remove TWA promise apps that failed web app install
entry.content:
Currently, the PromiseAppService gets notified about successful TWA

installations via the call to observers with

AppRegistryCache::OnAppUpdate. This allows the PromiseAppService to

get the correct PackageId and mark the appropriate promise app as

PromiseStatus::kSuccess to trigger a replacement animation for

transitioning the Launcher/ Shelf promise item into the installed app

item. However, in the event that the ARC package is successfully

downloaded from the Play Store but the web app installation fails, the

PromiseAppService never gets an update because the app never reaches

the AppRegistryCache.



To cover the case of failed web app installation, this CL makes the

ApkWebAppService update the PromiseAppService when any installation

attempt finishes. The PromiseAppService can now mark the failed

installations as kCancelled so that the client knows that there won't

have to be any replacement animation to transition to an installed app

item.

entry.title: [CloudOpenMetrics] Eagerly dump state for inconsistency found in flow
entry.content:
When an inconsistency is found during the cloud open/upload flow

or during the post-processing in the CloudOpenMetrics destructor, Chrome

error logs are printed. The former Chrome logs were lost in the crash

report as DumpWithoutCrashing() was called in the destructor and only

the tail of Chrome logs are included.



To fix this, immediately call DumpWithoutCrashing() during any

inconsistencies found during the cloud open/upload flow. Continue to

DumpWithoutCrashing() at the end of the destructor when any

inconsistencies are found there.



Rename PrintDebugInformation() to OnInconsistencyFound() as it is more

description. Extend this to include a `immediately_dump` argument

which determines if eager dumping of the state should occur.

entry.title: Properly mark new installs with promise apps
entry.content:
When app installation with a promise item completes, the promise item

attributes are transferred to a sync item for the installed app,

creating a sync item when needed. Creating a sync item may interfere

with logic to detect "new installs", which marks an app as a new install

only if a sync item for the app does not yet exist. This adds an

"is_new" property to AppListSyncableService::SyncItem, which can be used

to detect "new" apps for which a sync item has been created before they

were added to app service (as may be the case for apps that have a

promise icon).

entry.title: [PageColors] Add page colors theme options to the forced colors key
entry.content:
Page colors is a browser setting that enables users to toggle forced

colors mode at the browser level, instead of relying on an OS setting.

This gives users more control over this feature and allows them to use

it on different operating systems, not just Windows.



This CL extends the ForcedColors ColorProviderKey to include four page

colors theme options : `Dusk`, `Desert`, `Black`, `White`. These

options will enable us to apply different contrast themes via mixers

based on the user's preferences. This is part of our goal of having a

browser option to trigger forced colors mode.



This CL does not change any functionality. In future CLs, we will

integrate page colors to the native theme, implement the mixer, and add

a block list to allow users to opt out of forced colors for certain

sites.

NetworkServiceProxyDelegate::OnTunnelHeadersReceived via

the SocketParams objects have been constructed to support

nested proxies. Some associated changes were necessary to get

this passing, specifically modifying some DCHECKs and adding

a secure_dns_policy member to HttpProxySocketParams.

such as ssl_connect_job_unittest.cc where we now create

params similarly to how it's done in

http_proxy_connect_job_unittest.cc. In both I was able

to re-use existing helper methods for a DoH test.

entry.title: Make kIdleThicknessScale have a single definition.
entry.content:
Currently kIdleThicknessScale is defined in many different places

across the code base[1]. This is obviously bad for maintenance.



This CL moves the definition to a single source of truth in

ui/native_theme/overlay_scrollbar_constants_aura.h



I removed three redefinitions of the variable:

1. ScrollbarThinningController: The thickness scale is now a setting of

the layer_tree_settings and is passed through the animation controller's

constructors.

2. PaintedScrollbarLayerImpl: The thickness scale is now queried from

layer tree settings.

3. ScrollbarThemeFluent: "default thickness scale" has been added as a

parameter of `ScrollbarStyle` and is now queried from the web theme

engine.



The variable still has to be redefined in unittests that want to use it,

but this is already the case with the other constants defined in the

aura constants file[2].





[1] https://source.chromium.org/search?q=%22kIdleThicknessScale%20%3D%22%20-path:test&sq=

[2] https://source.chromium.org/search?q=(scrollbar_fade_duration%20OR%20scrollbar_fade_delay)%20AND%20path:test
